@odracci Interesting! So just making sure I understand what's happening here:

1. You launch minikube + the kubernetes airflow deployment
2. You launch a docker-compose job with all necessary binaries (kubectl, minikube, etc.) mounted as volumes + MINIKUBE_IP as an env variable
3. You run the tests in docker-compose but with the ability to hit the minikube cluster through both API + command line tools).

Let me know if I've missed anything because overall this is super cool :). 

